---
import SocialList from "@/components/SocialList.astro";
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import profile from "@/assets/profilepic.png";
---

<PageLayout meta={{ title: "Home" }}>
	<section>
		<div class="home-grid">
			<div class="home-image">
				<Image
					src={profile}
					alt="Hamza Mooraj"
					width={220}
					height={220}
					class="profile-img"
				/>
			</div>

			<div class="home-text">
				<h1 class="title mb-3">Hello!</h1>

				<div class="mb-8">
					<SocialList />
				</div>

				<p class="mb-5 text-base sm:text-lg">
					I’m an AI engineer and researcher with a strong interest in how intelligent systems behave under real-world constraints,
					particularly when multimodality, retrieval, long-horizon interaction, and deployment conditions affect
					reliability. I graduated from Heriot-Watt University in 2025 with First-Class Honours in BSc Computer
					Science (Artificial Intelligence).
				</p>

				<p class="mb-5 text-base sm:text-lg">
					My current research centres on empirical evaluation of model behaviour across realistic conditions. In my
					crop disease classification work, I developed AgriPath-LF16, a benchmark with explicit lab–field domain
					separation, and used it to study trade-offs across CNNs, contrastive vision-language models, and
					generative vision-language models under different training regimes.
				</p>

				<p class="mb-5 text-base sm:text-lg">
					I have also worked on applied AI systems, including the development and deployment of a retrieval-augmented
					“Learning Buddy” for the Heriot-Watt student portal. More broadly, my experience spans multimodal systems,
					RAG pipelines, evaluation workflows, and software development across research, academic, and industry
					settings.
				</p>

				<p class="mb-5 text-base sm:text-lg">
					My broader interests lie in agentic and multimodal AI systems, especially questions of monitoring,
					reliability, safe behaviour under deployment constraints, and the evaluation of systems operating over time
					in complex environments.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<style>
		.home-grid {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: 2rem;
			align-items: start;
		}

		@media (min-width: 768px) {
			.home-grid {
				grid-template-columns: 240px 1fr;
			}
		}

		.home-image {
			display: flex;
			justify-content: center;
		}

		@media (min-width: 768px) {
			.home-image {
				justify-content: flex-start;
			}
		}

		.profile-img {
			border-radius: 999px;
			border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
		}
	</style>
</PageLayout>